OL,3,CWill some protests be banned? Home
OL,4,Csecretary exploring options
OL,6,FSeveral pieces of legislation already
OL,7,Fexist to limit people's right to
OL,8,Fprotest, something which is protected
OL,9,Funder the Human Rights Act 1998, as
OL,10,F"freedom of expression", and "freedom
OL,11,Fof peaceful assembly".
OL,13,FThe Public Order Act, gives law
OL,14,Fenforcement the ability to dictate the
OL,15,Froute of a march, prohibit it from
OL,16,Fentering a particular area, or make it
OL,17,Fa static protest instead.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
