PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777680175
OL,3,CWill some protests be banned? Home
OL,4,Csecretary exploring options
OL,6,FThe Police, Crime, Sentencing and
OL,7,FCourts Act 2022, goes further,
OL,8,Fallowing police to consider the
OL,9,Fcumulative effects of protest and
OL,10,Fnoise when assessing the risk of
OL,11,F"serious unease" or "more than minor
OL,12,Fdisruption".
OL,14,FThe Crime and Policing Bill, which
OL,15,Freceived royal assent on April 29,
OL,16,Fadds more, including a blanket ban on
OL,17,Fface coverings at protests,
OL,18,Frestrictions on gatherings near places
OL,19,Fof worship, and new protections making
OL,20,Fit a criminal offence to protest
OL,21,Foutside an MPs' or councillors' home.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
